			>
			<DIV></DIV><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
pink187 wrote:<BR>
<DIV><BR>I've heard the argument "wait and see what the pve progression server does."&nbsp; I have to wonder why?&nbsp; What does that have to do with the potential of a pvp server?</DIV>
<DIV>If anything the numbers will be skewed.&nbsp; How many people will leave the Pve serve if/once a pvp server is launched?&nbsp; I'm guessing a whole lot.&nbsp; So trying to determine the need of a pvp </DIV>
<DIV>server based off numbers of a pve server is silly.</DIV>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>If the PvE progression server doesn't pan out, it is highly doubtful that a PvP server will since PvE has a greater chance for long success.&nbsp; A PvP server will fall apart when Plane of Knowledge gets added and gear/AAs get out of hand.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>You've seen no evidence?&nbsp; What research have you done that has led you to believe that you don't see the demand for that type of server?&nbsp; I'm genuinely curious.</DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The fact that all i've heard is the same few people claim they have tons of friends who will reactivate if they create a PvP server is not evidence of the potential success of said PvP server.<BR>	
