			<DIV></DIV>The thing is, also, that just as the bluebies have their idea of which expansion ruined things for them, PvPers also have the same idea. The population of a progressive PvP server might be high for a little while, but as soon as PoP comes out, and people start insta-gating away from you again, or certain clickies become available that are considered unbalancing in PvP, or the population gets spread too thin that you can't find anyone to kill, everyone will leave. Seeing the determination to push ahead is so much stronger on the PvP servers (Rallos was the only server that could get the people together to kill Sleeper, remember) the content should be unlocked a lot faster there by the highest portion of the population than on any blue server. So for the sake of a few months of good PvP, only to have the server die with PoP, is it really worth it in the long run to open another server??	
