		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<P>There are a&nbsp;lot more reasons&nbsp;for why current Zek has low population than simple disinterest in PvP.</P>
<P>Primary among them, the same expanding of the game that has inflated the game in PvE with many dire consequences also threw PvP way out of balance.&nbsp;&nbsp;Few things&nbsp;will kill PvP faster than balance issues.&nbsp; It's a problem for PvE.&nbsp; It's absolute death for PvP.&nbsp; A classic or progression PvP server would go a long way to fix that.</P>
<P>Another serious problem, I'm told (it wasn't when I last played PvP) is cheaters using 3rd party cheats.&nbsp; It happens on all servers, but in PvE it just gives the cheater an unfair advantage....In PvP it just kills the entire thing.&nbsp; Which is why PvP-centric games like DAoC have a team that actively pursues and bans cheaters and a set of devs that code the game to sniff them out.&nbsp; DAoC has a miniscule playerbase compared to other games like EQ, yet they have no compunction at all about banning several hundred cheaters in one day.&nbsp; They don't do this just out of principle....They do it because like imbalances, few factors are total death to PvP than cheating.&nbsp; SoE will have to get proactive about dealing with these people if they are serious about making EQ PvP work.</P>
<P>But don't fool yourself.&nbsp; PvP is plenty popular and PvPers are looking for a good game to PvP in.......Problem is so many games are either lousy games or have lousy implementations of PvP or both.&nbsp; At the moment, EQ falls under the "lousy implementation" category.&nbsp; But they can take strides in the right direction with PvP Progression or Classic as a lot of the balance issues with EQ PvP weren't as pronounced until the game was expanded.</P>
<P>In fact, PvE is a rather new concept in gaming, not the other way around.&nbsp; I've been computer gaming for 25+ years and only in the last 10 or so has most AI even been worth playing against.&nbsp; Before that you ALWAYS chose to play games that could be played against another player....On mainframe.....Turn based on a PC....on a network....turnbased email....Whatever.&nbsp; A lot of times you would play games that weren't as good or were just text instead of flashier games&nbsp;available simply because it allowed some sort of play against another human.</P>	
		</td></tr>
