			>
			<div></div><div><br><blockquote><hr>Massimo_Bertoxx wrote:<br><div></div><p>There are a&nbsp;lot more reasons&nbsp;for why current Zek has low population than simple disinterest in PvP.</p><p>Primary among them, the same expanding of the game that has inflated the game in PvE with many dire consequences also threw PvP way out of balance.&nbsp;&nbsp;Few things&nbsp;will kill PvP faster than balance issues.&nbsp; It's a problem for PvE.&nbsp; It's absolute death for PvP.&nbsp; A classic or progression PvP server would go a long way to fix that.</p><p>Another serious problem, I'm told (it wasn't when I last played PvP) is cheaters using 3rd party cheats.&nbsp; It happens on all servers, but in PvE it just gives the cheater an unfair advantage....In PvP it just kills the entire thing.&nbsp; Which is why PvP-centric games like DAoC have a team that actively pursues and bans cheaters and a set of devs that code the game to sniff them out.&nbsp; DAoC has a miniscule playerbase compared to other games like EQ, yet they have no compunction at all about banning several hundred cheaters in one day.&nbsp; They don't do this just out of principle....They do it because like imbalances, few factors are total death to PvP than cheating.&nbsp; SoE will have to get proactive about dealing with these people if they are serious about making EQ PvP work.</p><p>But don't fool yourself.&nbsp; PvP is plenty popular and PvPers are looking for a good game to PvP in.......Problem is so many games are either lousy games or have lousy implementations of PvP or both.&nbsp; At the moment, EQ falls under the "lousy implementation" category.&nbsp; But they can take strides in the right direction with PvP Progression or Classic as a lot of the balance issues with EQ PvP weren't as pronounced until the game was expanded.</p><p>In fact, PvE is a rather new concept in gaming, not the other way around.&nbsp; I've been computer gaming for 25+ years and only in the last 10 or so has most AI even been worth playing against.&nbsp; Before that you ALWAYS chose to play games that could be played against another player....On mainframe.....Turn based on a PC....on a network....turnbased email....Whatever.&nbsp; A lot of times you would play games that weren't as good or were just text instead of flashier games&nbsp;available simply because it allowed some sort of play against another human.</p><br><hr></blockquote><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;And again, alot of what you speak will not change that much with a progression server.<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;What is needed to keep pvp balances as far as content is a "classic" version.<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;That way there will not be any truely overpowering items in the game.<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;As far as hackers, ect that wouldn't change for a new server either inless those hackers/cheaters<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;get banned. Infact a new pvp server may attacts them even more for verious reasons.&nbsp;<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;And truth be told Everquest was a first of its kind. EQ really started the trend of the MMORPG.&nbsp;<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Sure there was UO and muds but the technology wasn't there to do what EQ did for the<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;games older then EQ.&nbsp;<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Sure there was Quake and Doom but those were first person shooters. It's, as i understand,<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;a bit harder to make a MMORPG like EQ then it would be for a first person shooter.<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Or atleast it may have been back then.<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oh, and if you wanted to experience a really good pvp rpg game back then there was <b>underlight</b>.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Now that was a mmorpg game that you needed some skills in pvp with. And you <b>had </b>to roleplay<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;to advance.<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Anyways enough about that and going off topic.&nbsp;<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;I think thats most of the problem. This game has changed so much and has been expanded to an extent<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;that some mechanics of the game such as pvp kinda got left behind in some respects.<br></div>	
