<P><BR>But this is not the large portion of the Everquest demographic.</P>
<P>A TV show like CSI doesnt really appeal to the 20-25 crowd.&nbsp; They dont really try to get&nbsp;those viewers (despite them being a huge portion fo the TV viewers) because they have their niche crowd.</P>
<P>EQ appeals mainly to older gamers.&nbsp; Mostly late 20s through mid 30s.&nbsp; this is NOT a huge PvP demographic.&nbsp; In fact, most of these people don't care fi its even in the game (though some will participate in light, occasional pvp if its there.)</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>EQ would be smart to play towards its market, and thats what it has done.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>now that doesnt mean for sure that there shouldnt be a PvP progression server, but when people are asking for stuff like removal of instances (which would cut down probably 1/3 of the population right away when they learn a lot fo PvE content is disapperaing) SoE has to look at it and think 'is it worth it?'</P>
<P>Plus they also know that it would kill Zek as a great deal fo the popualtion would flock to this server.&nbsp; So what do they dow ith Zeks erver?&nbsp; theres nowhere left for it to merge.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>Im not against the idea of giving the PvPers a new server, I just question the LONG TERM feasibility of it.</P>
