			<div></div>People have mentioned it before but there is a sure fire way for all those who want a PvP Progression server to cast a vote and show the devs that there is viable interest for one.<br><br>Talk to a Priest of Discord, turn in your book, and play exclusively a red character on The Combine.<br><br>Once the number of red players reaches a critical mass, others will do the same since they know there are players out there to group with and maybe the reds will outnumber the blues one day.&nbsp; What would happen next if the reds begin to outnumber the blues?&nbsp; I tell you what would happen, the blues would join us in a call for a PvP Progression server.&nbsp; The blues would be the ones that have a hard time getting a group.&nbsp; Ever think of that?<br><br>Problem is that is there enough gutsy players out there that want a PvP Progression server to do this and stick with it to make it happen?<br><br>If you want a PvP Progression server, ask yourself these questions:&nbsp; Will you just post about how you want one or will you do something about it to make it happen?&nbsp; Will you wait for it to happen by playing it safe and staying blue or will you stick your neck out?&nbsp; Will you be a leader or a follower?<br><br>Forget about PvP on this server if you roll a red.&nbsp; That is not the point of doing it on this server.&nbsp; Roll a red to support the idea and each other that want the same thing, ie. a PvP Progression server.<br><br>I for one will roll a red cleric as my main to support the red population and the idea it represents.&nbsp; Once I create him, I will post his name and any red player is more than welcome to group.<br><br>I call on everyone who wants a PvP Progression server to roll red mains, group with each other, and <b>NOT </b>PvP each other.&nbsp; Together we will make the red population grow and one day outnumber the blues.&nbsp; Together we do have the power.&nbsp; Together, we can make the dream come true.<br><br>I thank you.<br><div