			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<P>Okay, I've been following along with the various pvp pro or con discussion threads and really, I don't see what the big deal is.&nbsp; I have no idea why standard rule set server players are opposed to a PvP prog server.&nbsp; I can see why SOE might not want to offer one if there aren't enough players to make it worthwhile, but as far as Blue server players arguing against it, that just doesn't make any sense to me.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>I'm not a big PvP player, done it, it's okay I guess, but I don't find it more or less fun than playing on a regular server, just different.&nbsp; It's just that I have a lot of friends on blue servers and only 1 or 2 on Zek who play only sporadically. so I stick to standard servers for the most part.&nbsp; But I just don't understand all this angst about to PvP or not to PvP.&nbsp; When Combine goes live, make a statement.&nbsp; Just turn in your books, put the naysayers on /ignore and get on with it.&nbsp; If there are enough people make a showing who are interested in a pvp prog server, then I am sure soe will open one up.&nbsp; And for the blue players who are opposed to PvP, get over it.</P>	
