		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>And this is the problem of having PvP in a game that wasn't designed to be solely a PvP style game. Anytime something changes on the blue servers, it changes something on the red servers and vice versa. What is good game on a blue server does not always make for good game on a red server and vice versa. To balance all the classes on the red servers so that no class is superior to any other class, means that those changes will carry over to PvE and leave some classes super strong and other classes totally gimped. You can't have it both ways. Either the game gets balanced for PvE or it gets balanced for PvP, and since more players play on the blue servers than on Zek, guess which it gets balanced for?	
		</td></tr>
